cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY

This paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation in natural language processing, specifically in the context of classifying social media posts during a crisis event. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel model that uses adversarial learning and graph embeddings, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and data mining, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also likely categories. The paper also deals with semi-supervised learning, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
